cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV. 

This paper focuses on the development of a deep learning model for predicting the forces a garment will apply to a person's body during robot-assisted dressing. This involves the use of haptic and kinematic observations from the robot's end effector, which are relevant to the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The goal of the research is to improve the quality of life for people with disabilities, which is relevant to the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of simulation data for training the model is also relevant to the field of machine learning (cs.LG), and the evaluation of the approach involves image analysis of the robot's performance, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV).
